    <rigor-reason>The `sprk_gate_approval` entity is the queue table consumed by `DataversePrecedentBoardGateResolver`; status field drives the resume-on-approval lifecycle for paused Action runs; mis-shaped gate types or status states force rework across Phase 3 (4 resolvers)</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches only `sprk_gate_approval` entity definition; disjoint from tasks 010 (action entities), 011 (sprk_toolregistry), 013 (sprk_aichatcontextmap)</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create the `sprk_gate_approval` Dataverse entity — the queue table consumed by `DataversePrecedentBoardGateResolver` (Phase 3) and surfaced via `GateApprovalCard` Fluent v9 component. Carries the five gate types (`EthicsCritical`, `MeaningCritical`, `FinalDelivery`, `EngagementAcceptance`, `TeamSelection`) plus `Custom`, a status field that drives the resume-on-approval flow, and tenant scoping (NFR-05).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE Dataverse schema engineer with experience modeling queue-style entities (status-driven, polled-or-webhook-resumed). You understand the gate-resolution flow: Action run pauses → `sprk_gate_approval` record written → user approves/rejects via UI or webhook → run resumes or terminates with reason.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `sprk_gate_approval` entity exists in dev with these fields:

    1. **`approvalId`** — Text (primary name); GUID
    2. **`runId`** — Lookup → `sprk_actionrun`; the paused run awaiting this gate
    3. **`gateType`** — Choice: EthicsCritical, MeaningCritical, FinalDelivery, EngagementAcceptance, TeamSelection, Custom
    4. **`status`** — Choice: Pending, Approved, Rejected, TimedOut
    5. **`requestedAt`** — DateTime
    6. **`requestedBy`** — Lookup → SystemUser (the user/agent requesting approval)
    7. **`resolvedAt`** — DateTime, nullable
    8. **`resolvedBy`** — Lookup → SystemUser, nullable (the approver/rejecter)
    9. **`reason`** — Text(Memo); rejection reason or approval rationale
    10. **`contextPayloadJson`** — Text(Memo); JSON: the gate's input context (what's being approved)
    11. **`gateConfigJson`** — Text(Memo); JSON: gate-specific config (timeout, resolver type, callback URL)
    12. **`timeoutAt`** — DateTime; computed `requestedAt + 5min` default per spec FR-17 (configurable via gateConfigJson)
    13. **`tenantId`** — Text; tenant scoping (NFR-05)
    14. **`correlationId`** — Text; for audit + log correlation with parent run

    Entity packed into the same solution as task 010 + 011 entities. Deliverable: 2 sample records created (one Pending, one Approved), confirming all fields are usable.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The gate approval flow per spec FR-17 + design §5:
      1. Action run hits a gate (e.g., `humanGate = true` on a `SendEmail` Tool)
      2. The `IGateResolver` impl (Phase 3) writes a `sprk_gate_approval` record with status = Pending, gateType = ..., timeoutAt = now + 5 min
      3. UI (`GateApprovalCard`) or webhook caller reads the record, prompts the user
      4. User approves → status flips to Approved; run resumes (resolver detects via poll or webhook)
      5. User rejects → status flips to Rejected with reason; run terminates with reason
      6. Timeout (5 min default) → status flips to TimedOut → auto-reject

      The 5-minute default timeout is a hard spec requirement (FR-17). It is stored as `timeoutAt` (computed DateTime) so a sweeper job can scan for expired pending records and flip them to TimedOut.

      The four resolver implementations (`DataversePrecedentBoardGateResolver`, `InteractiveGateResolver`, `WebhookGateResolver`, `AutoApproveGateResolver`) all WRITE to this entity. The first two also poll/listen on it for status transitions. `WebhookGateResolver` writes initially then receives external callback. `AutoApproveGateResolver` writes with status = Approved immediately (audit trail without user interaction).

      Gate types per spec scope section: `EthicsCritical`, `MeaningCritical`, `FinalDelivery`, `EngagementAcceptance`, `TeamSelection`, plus `Custom`. Do NOT add new gate types without spec amendment.

      Tenant scoping: `tenantId` text field, required. Cross-tenant gate visibility forbidden (NFR-05).
    </background>
