  <notes>
    The gate status state machine (`Pending → Approved | Rejected | TimedOut`) is **separate from** the run status state machine in `sprk_actionrun` (which follows ADR-017). Don't confuse them. A run that hits a gate stays in `Running` status; only after the gate resolves does the run transition to `Completed`, `Failed`, or back to `Running` (for subsequent steps).

    The 5-minute timeout default is a hard spec requirement (FR-17). DO NOT make it shorter or longer without spec amendment. It is configurable per-Action via `gateConfigJson.timeoutOverride`, but the entity default is 5 min.

    A sweeper job (Phase 3) will scan for expired Pending records every minute or so and flip them to TimedOut. The entity just stores `timeoutAt`; the sweeper logic lives in BFF.

    `coordination-assessment-with-insights-engine.md` notes joint ownership of the gate primitive. Insights Engine will CONSUME `IGateResolver` (and write to this entity), not redefine it. Action Engine defines it canonically.

    Do NOT add plugins to auto-resolve gates or flip statuses. The resolver layer in BFF (Phase 3) handles all state transitions per ADR-002.
  </notes>

